# 🎵 Deezer Music Explorer

A simple web app to search, preview, and manage music tracks using a **local JSON server**.  
Built with **HTML, CSS, and JavaScript**.

---

 <!-- Features -->

- 🔍 Search songs by title or artist.
- 🎼 Filter results by artist name.
- ▶ Preview and play songs with a global audio player.
- ❤️ Add tracks to a playlist section.
- 🌙 Toggle between **Dark / Light mode** (background image remains intact).
- 🎨 Responsive layout with custom styling.

---

<!-- Project Structure -->

.
├── index.html # Main HTML file
├── style.css # Styling (light/dark themes, layout, etc.)
├── index.js # JavaScript logic (fetch, search, filter, playlist, theme toggle)
├── db.json # Local JSON database of songs
├── music/ # Folder for local mp3 files
│ ├── alone.mp3
│ ├── commas.mp3
│ └── ...
└── images/ # Folder for cover images
├── brettyoung.jpg
├── inauma.jpg
└── ...

 <!-- Example db.json -->

``json
{
"songs": [
{
"id": 1,
"title": "alone",
"artist": "Alan Walker",
"album": "Divide",
"preview": "music/alone.mp3",
"cover": "https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/4/45/Divide_cover.png"
},
{
"id": 2,
"title": "commas",
"artist": "Ayra Star",
"album": "21",
"preview": "music/commas.mp3",
"cover": "https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/1/1b/Ayra Star_-_21.png"
},
{
"id": 9,
"title": "incaseyoudidntknow",
"artist": "Brett Young",
"album": "Brett Young",
"preview": "music/incaseyoudidntknow.mp3",
"cover": "images/brettyoung.jpg"
}
]
}

<!-- Setup & Run -->

️- Install JSON Server
-npm install -g json-server

️-Run JSON Server
-json-server --watch db.json --port 3000

The API will now be available at:

<!-- http://localhost:3000/songs -->

- Open in Browser

Just open index.html in your browser.

<!-- Usage -->

Enter a search term (song title / artist) → click Search.

Use Filter Results to narrow down by artist name.

Click ▶ Play to listen to a preview.

Click ➕ Add to save the track into your playlist.

Toggle between 🌙 Dark / ☀️ Light mode (background image remains).

<!-- Notes -->

Make sure your music/ and images/ folders exist and match the paths in db.json.

If a track does not play, check the preview path or use a valid external .mp3 URL.

Ports: Default is 3000, but you can change it:

<!-- Tech Stack -->

HTML5

CSS3

JavaScript (ES6+)

JSON Server

